dfischer.utils

Class HttpLoadTestUserContextTable

  • java.lang.Object
    • dfischer.utils.HttpLoadTestUserContextTable

  • public class HttpLoadTestUserContextTable
extends java.lang.Object
    A table of contexts for all simulated users of the load test program. The integrity of this table must be protected by a read/write lock. Before accessing the (internal) ArrayList of user contexts, you have first to acquire the read lock or the write lock. The write lock is only needed if elements are added to or removed from the ArrayList of user contexts - or when the method HttpLoadTestUserContext.setLoadTestUserFinallyEnded() is called. For all other operations a read lock is always enough - even if you modify data of one or several user contexts. Rule of thumb: you need normally only a read lock.
    Since:
    V5.2-O
    See Also:
    HttpLoadTestUserContext.setLoadTestUserFinallyEnded()
